# 5. ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\
\
## 5.1 Governor A: Explain Cap\
- [ ] Validator detects when EXPLAIN count > 1 for same insight in same chapter\
- [ ] Violation includes: beat_id, template_path, line_number, insight_id, counts\
- [ ] Exit code 1 on any EXPLAIN cap violation\
\
## 5.2 Governor B: Demo Saturation\
- [ ] Validator detects when DEMONSTRATE count > 3 for same insight in same chapter\
- [ ] Default behavior: WARN (exit 0)\
- [ ] Strict mode: FAIL (exit 1)\
- [ ] Violation includes: beat_id, template_path, line_number, insight_id, counts\
\
## 5.3 Governor C: Duplication Guard\
- [ ] Validator detects blocks with >80% similarity and >3 lines\
- [ ] Comparison is within-chapter only\
- [ ] Violation includes: beat_id, template_path, duplicate_of, similarity score\
- [ ] Exit code 1 on any duplication violation\
\
## 5.4 Governor D: Truncation Guard\
- [ ] Validator detects incomplete words at end of beats\
- [ ] Catches patterns: "You notice yo.", orphan periods, unclosed quotes\
- [ ] Violation includes: beat_id, template_path, pattern_matched, text_fragment\
- [ ] Exit code 1 on any truncation violation\
\
## 5.5 Report Format\
- [ ] JSON output includes all required fields per violation\
- [ ] Human-readable output shows actionable beat IDs and file paths\
- [ ] Report grouped by governor type\
\
## 5.6 Integration\
- [ ] CLI returns exit code 0 on pass, 1 on fail\
- [ ] Can be run in CI/CD pipeline\
- [ ] Violations point to template file, not generated output\
\
